Add @butter{1/2%cup}, @white sugar{1.5%cups}, @packed brown sugar{1/2%cup}, @milk{1/2%cup}, @cocoa{4%tbsp}, and @kosher salt{1%pinch} into a #4-quart sauce pan{}.
Bring to a rolling boil and hold for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add @creamy peanut butter{1/2%cup} into the hot mixture and stir until melted.
Add in @vanilla{2%tsp}.  (Almond extract is good also, but recommend only using 1/2 teaspoon almond extract with 1 1/2 tsp vanilla extract.)
Mix in @dry quick-cooking oats{3%cups} until they are completely coated.
Drop cookies by tablespoonfuls onto #wax paper{}.
Let cool until set.